== Bidirectional Scripts in Desktop Software ==

=== Readings (a.k.a. References) ===

 * [http://www.unicode.org/reports/tr9/ Unicode Bidirectional Algorithm] is the place to start.  It contains the basic algorithm to map a Unicode plain text string to a visual ordering.

 * [http://behdad.org/download/Presentations/bidi-layouts/ Bidirectional Layouts in GTK+] is a presentation of the state of art bidirectional support in Gtk+ by mid 2004.  Discusses several problems and concepts that are general to all GUI applications.

 * [http://cben-hacks.sourceforge.net/bidi/hibidi.html Hierarchically Implicit Bidi] is a personal proposal for a hierarchical bidirectional system.

 *[http://imagic.weizmann.ac.il/~dov/Hebrew/logicUI24.htm Guidelines of a Logical User Interface for Editing Bidirectional Text] (also [http://www-306.ibm.com/software/globalization/topics/bidiui/index.jsp here]) is the guidelines in use by IBM.

 * [http://bidiui.mozdev.org/ Mozilla BiDi UI Extension] is a Mozilla extension to support bidirectional widgets on Mozilla user interface.

 * [http://yudit.org/bidi/ Yudit Bidirectional Information] discusses different security problems with bidirectional text support.

 * [http://www.w3.org/International/iri-edit/ Editing 'Internationalized Resource Identifiers (IRIs)']

 * [http://www.langbox.com/AraMosaic/mozilla/BiDi_API.html Mozilla Bi-Di API proposal] (out-dated) is the old proposal to add support for bidirectional text to Mozilla.  Note that the API proposed in this document is missing essential features, like line breaking support.

 * The [http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#direction unicode-bidi and direction] attribute definitions in CSS, and it's [http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/box.html#q11 box model].

=== Non-Readings (a.k.a. Pre-Unicode Tries) ===

 * [http://www-306.ibm.com/software/webservers/hostondemand/library/v8infocenter/hod/en/help/bidi.html Understanding bidirectional language support] is an older IBM standard.

